                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4/301: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-28T11:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1921—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 23—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>396. Diplomatic Advisory Council met yesterday as stated in my 392. It did not
                    conclude its sessions. They will be resumed tomorrow.</p>
                <p>The subject matter of your 199, November 19, is one of the questions being
                    discussed. I have talked much with leaders and can see no reason for making
                    great concessions to Kato as here strongest desire is for an agreement. If Kato
                    takes an extreme position, I do not believe he will eventually [be]
                    supported.</p>
                <p>You might inform me concerning the present status so that I can more
                    intelligently discuss the matter upon conclusion of meeting of Diplomatic
                    Advisory Council.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
